# 🧾 ✅ GitHub Actions Workflow Structure

```yaml
name: Workflow Name

on:
  workflow_dispatch:

env:
  GLOBAL_VAR: value

jobs:
  job1:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    needs: job0

    env:
      JOB_VAR: value

    outputs:
      output_name: ${{ steps.step_id.outputs.value }}

    steps:
      - name: Step Name
        id: step_id
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Run command
        run: echo "Hello"

      - name: Conditional step
        if: ${{ success() }}

      - name: Set output
        run: echo "value=test" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
```

***

# 📦 ✅ ALL PARAMETERS EXPLAINED

***

# 🔹 1. `name`

```yaml
name: My Workflow
```

👉 Workflow name (shown in UI)

***

# 🔹 2. `on` (Triggers)

```yaml
on:
  push:
  pull_request:
  workflow_dispatch:
  schedule:
    - cron: "0 0 * * *"
```

👉 Defines when workflow runs

| Trigger            | Use       |
| ------------------ | --------- |
| push               | code push |
| pull\_request      | PR events |
| workflow\_dispatch | manual    |
| schedule           | cron jobs |

***

# 🔹 3. `env`

```yaml
env:
  APP_NAME: entrust
```

👉 Environment variables  
✅ Can be at:

* workflow level
* job level
* step level

***

# 🔹 4. `jobs`

```yaml
jobs:
  build:
```

👉 Defines tasks (parallel or sequential)

***

# 🔹 5. `runs-on`

```yaml
runs-on: ubuntu-latest
```

👉 Runner machine

| Value          | Meaning |
| -------------- | ------- |
| ubuntu-latest  | Linux   |
| windows-latest | Windows |
| macos-latest   | macOS   |

***

# 🔹 6. `needs`

```yaml
needs: job1
```

👉 Job dependency  
✅ Ensures order execution

***

# 🔹 7. `steps`

```yaml
steps:
```

👉 List of actions inside job

***

# 🔹 8. `name` (Step)

```yaml
- name: Install dependencies
```

👉 Step label

***

# 🔹 9. `id`

```yaml
id: build_step
```

👉 Used to reference outputs

***

# 🔹 10. `run`

```yaml
run: echo "Hello"
```

👉 Executes shell commands

✅ Multi-line:

```yaml
run: |
  echo "Hello"
  ls -l
```

***

# 🔹 11. `uses`

```yaml
uses: actions/checkout@v4
```

👉 Use prebuilt action

***

# 🔹 12. `with`

```yaml
with:
  path: ./app
```

👉 Inputs to action

***

# 🔹 13. `outputs` (Job level)

```yaml
outputs:
  name: ${{ steps.set.outputs.name }}
```

👉 Share data to other jobs

***

# 🔹 14. `$GITHUB_OUTPUT`

```bash
echo "key=value" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT
```

👉 Set step output

***

# 🔹 15. `if` (Conditions)

```yaml
if: ${{ github.event_name == 'push' }}
```

👉 Run step/job conditionally

***

# 🔹 16. `secrets`

```yaml
${{ secrets.PASSWORD }}
```

👉 Secure values

***

# 🔹 17. `context`

```yaml
${{ github.actor }}
${{ runner.os }}
${{ env.APP_NAME }}
```

👉 Dynamic values

***

# 🔹 18. `timeout-minutes`

```yaml
timeout-minutes: 10
```

👉 Job timeout

***

# 🔹 19. `continue-on-error`

```yaml
continue-on-error: true
```

👉 Ignore failure

***

# 🔹 20. `strategy` (Matrix builds)

```yaml
strategy:
  matrix:
    node: [14, 16, 18]
```

👉 Run multiple configurations

***

# 🔹 21. `defaults`

```yaml
defaults:
  run:
    shell: bash
```

👉 Default shell settings

***

# 🔹 22. `permissions`

```yaml
permissions:
  contents: read
```

👉 GitHub token permissions

***

# 🔹 23. `concurrency`

```yaml
concurrency:
  group: deploy
  cancel-in-progress: true
```

👉 Prevent parallel runs

***

# 🔹 24. `environment`

```yaml
environment: production
```

👉 Link to GitHub environment (with secrets, approvals)

***

# 🔹 25. `services`

```yaml
services:
  mysql:
    image: mysql:5.7
```

👉 Run containers inside job

***

# 🔹 26. `container`

```yaml
container:
  image: node:18
```

👉 Run job inside container

***

# 🔹 27. `defaults.run.working-directory`

```yaml
defaults:
  run:
    working-directory: ./app
```

***

# 🔹 28. `artifacts`

```yaml
- uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
  with:
    name: logs
    path: logs/
```

👉 Share files between jobs

***

# 🔹 29. `workflow_call` (Reusable workflows)

```yaml
on:
  workflow_call:
```

👉 Reusable workflows

***

# 🔹 30. `inputs` (for workflow\_dispatch)

```yaml
on:
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      env:
        description: "Environment"
        required: true
```

👉 User inputs

